<br>
Let me explain this a little better...yes Yeli is rooted in place, but he does summon.  I have sat at his gate with no one backing me up and sat there to unload my full manabar.  Instead of summoning me after damaging him, he didn't aggro and just instantly regen'd the lost hp and completely ignore me.<br>
<br>
If your wizards are getting eaten by ANY DB-able dragon short of a battle that you lose, then I have no clue wtf they're doing because I Can't get myself killed even if I try to.  Gozzrem, Telk, etc, I nuke from the moment the tanks charge to the moment the mob dies....I *never* get summoned.  So let me say this again so maybe you'll understand...As long as Someone who is aggro is in melee range I Will Not Get Hurt.  On a botched attempt at Gozz(so taking him on with 24 is bad with only 1 DB wiz..who knew?) I jumped out from behind the corner immediately after the first AE and blasted him, and kept unloading/medding/jumping back to refresh crap buffs before losing hp/resists.  Yes I died that attempt, but only because pretty much everyone did.  On the mob's hate list I was just in front of the clerics so the moment the last person in melee range went down I got destroyed, not before.  Even when the first main tank had died after I had already done 16k.<br>
