  Now onto our lovely charmed giant topic.  I decided to check over that lump of posts in the UI ? Zland thread and I did not see one mention from me about using pets...what are you talking about kani?  Maybe i'm a little too polite so my point often isnt as clear as I'd like it to be.  So i'll try to be a little more blunt.  *I* have felt that using pets during the pet aggro bug was a crutch.  Why do i feel that?  Not because pets are necessarily bad but because they rather unbalanced the high end encounters in kael.  Why didn't we use pets on these mobs during this time period?  Pretty much not because we want to take the &quot;high road&quot; but rather because we saw this nerf coming from a mile away and didnt want to get lulled into fighting complatency fighting mobs far below their normal &quot;challenge&quot;.  What about using golems on dain? Its something we always used and that was long before any aggro bug which caused said golem to tank the majority of the fight instead of only part of the time as an assist.  Did you guys use pets during this period to tackle the high end mobs in kael? I guess you did since you get highly defensive whenever any posts were made about tormax/kael mobs. Do I really care? No I don't, how you fight is your business not mine.  If you feel you have something to prove by fighting tormax/statue/whoever without these pets that is also your business and I never said anything to that extent.  More power to you in all your victories.<br>
<br>
I'm sure plenty of flames will follow this but I was a bit tired of being jumped upon and accused of making all sorts of accusations.  If you're going to flame away at least take an hour or two to mull over what I said and didnt say before posting.  There are many people in MS that I like and I don't wish you harm in your endentures(sp?).<br>
<br>
Btw I have no idea what chuk posted on the FoH board but I guess I can't read about it now.<br>
