...in Kael.  I don't see any indication that this was a global change.  This was a temporary fix, which is pretty obvious to spot.  When a mob is too high of a level for Boltran's/Dictate you get a message saying the mob is out of the level range for the spell.  When you get a resist message, it means the mob made its resist check (but is still charmable).<br>
<br>
So what did they do to the Lego/Trooper type mobs?  They didn't change the spells themselves, otherwise we would get the message that the mob is out of level range and not just a simple resist.  I'm pretty sure the mobs were still slowable, so they didn't just make the upper tier giants immune to magic.  They didn't buff up the level of the giants.  They just made it so that they resist all charms...again Just in Kael.  Seems like it was a temporary fix because someone killed one of their hardest mobs.<br>
